OL,3,C100-year-old veteran speaks of sadness
OL,4,Cof comrades he lost
OL,6,FStill in excellent health and spirit -
OL,7,Fit was a chance to look back on the
OL,8,Fmemorable trip to France, and speaking
OL,9,Fat Bayeux War Cemetery in front of a
OL,10,Ftv audience totalling 2 million.
OL,12,FHe says he will never forget the
OL,13,Fcomrades he lost in 1944 and the
OL,14,Flosses suffered in his battalion.
OL,16,FRichard said: "When we went over, in
OL,17,Fmy company, there were about 130 chaps.
OL,19,F"When we finished in Hamburg when the
OL,20,Fwar finished, there were 19 of us. It
OL,21,Fhas to be told.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/5
