OL,3,C100-year-old veteran speaks of sadness
OL,4,Cof comrades he lost
OL,6,F"But I've been very lucky in life,
OL,7,FI've had a very wonderful life and I
OL,8,Fwouldn't change it."
OL,10,FHe will be wearing his poppy with
OL,11,Fpride on Remembrance Day, with
OL,12,Fthoughts of his trip to Normandy in
OL,13,FJune in mind.
OL,15,FAnd not surprisingly, Richard still
OL,16,Fthinks he has one more trip to
OL,17,FNormandy left in him next summer.
